Title: On .NET Live- Multi-agent workflow using Azure Durable Functions and Semantic Kernel
Description:
Are you looking to implement durable, multi-agent systems for complex tasks across industries? In this week's episode, community MVP Divakar Kumar explores how to build a scalable, AI-driven travel planning app using Azure Durable Functions and Cosmos DB as the backbone for a robust, multi-agent real-time travel planning system.

Community Links: https://github.com/Cloud-Jas/DurableMultiAgents

Featuring: Divakar Kumar

#azure #cosmosdb #semantic-kernel

Title: Chromium Ozone/Wayland: The Last Mile Stretch
Description:
Hey there! I’m glad to finally start paying my blogging debt :) as this is something I’ve been planning to do for quite some time now. To get the ball rolling, I’ve shared some bits about me in my very first blog post Olá Mundo.
In this article, I’m going to walk through what we’ve been working on since last year in the Chromium Ozone/Wayland project, on which I’ve been involved (directly or indirectly) since I’ve joined Igalia back in 2018.
